{"lemma":"بِزٌّ","slug":"بِزٌّ","root":"ب.ز.ز","root_slug":"ب-ز-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ز-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2446"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B2%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"teat, mamma"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"garment, raiment, weed","tags":["regional"],"examples":[{"text":"قَدِمَ بَزٌّ مِنَ ٱلشَّامِ لِفُلَانٍ الْيَهُودِيِّ","english":"Some clothing arrived from the north for so-and-so, the Jew."},{"text":"قَالَ مَالِكٌ فِي الرَّجُلِ يَشْتَرِي الإِبِلَ أَوِ الْغَنَمَ أَوِ الْبَزَّ أَوِ الرَّقِيقَ أَوْ شَيْئًا مِنَ الْعُرُوضِ جِزَافًا إِنَّهُ لَا يَكُونُ الْجِزَافُ فِي شَىْءٍ مِمَّا يُعَدُّ عَدًّا.","english":"Malik said about a man who bought camels and sheep and clothing and slaves and any larger good without measuring precisely that there is no wholesale acquisition of a thing that can be counted."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strip off, to spoil, to remove by force","examples":[{"text":"مَن عَزَّ بَزَّ.","english":"He who overcomes takes the spoil."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَزَّ (bazza) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate to Aramaic בִּיזָא, ܒܷܙܐ (bizzā, “teat”), בּוּזָא (buzzā, “teat”), Ugaritic 𐎁𐎑 (bẓ, “teat”). Differently Akkadian 𒍣𒍣𒂊 (/⁠zīzu⁠/, “teat”), Hebrew זִיז (zīz, “abundance, teat, protuberance”), Hebrew דַּד (dad, “teat”), Aramaic דַּדָּא (daddā, “teat”).\n\nUltimately a re-borrowing from what was originally a Semitic source (Akkadian 𒁍𒌋𒋗 (bu-u-ṣu /⁠būṣu⁠/)); see also بِزَّة (bizza, “suit”).\n* Borrowed from Old Armenian բեհեզ (behez) or the earlier Old Armenian *բեեզ (*beez)\n* Alternatively, a clipping of بُزْيُون (buzyūn, “a kind of silk garment”), from Byzantine Greek βυσσίνη (bussínē), or from Ancient Greek βύσσος (bússos, “a very fine yellowish flax and the linen woven from it”).\n\nApparently denominal verb of بَزّ (bazz, “clothing”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2446","headword_ar":"بَزٌّ","root":"bz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of 1. (S, &c.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiYo'a","text_ar":"جِىْءَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi Eaz~aA baz~FA","text_ar":"بِهِ عَزَّا بَزًّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was brought without any means of avoiding it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"willingly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against his will:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ez","text_ar":"عز"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [as though originally signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by being overcome and despoiled."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cloths,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuffs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAb","text_ar":"ثِيَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAmb, Mgh, K:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biz~apN","text_ar":"بِزَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are the goods of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baz~aAz","text_ar":"بَزَّاز"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the merchant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furniture of a house or tent, consisting of cloths"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuffs"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAb","text_ar":"ثِيَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":", IDrd, Mgh, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) in the dial. of the people of El-Koofeh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cloths,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuffs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vyAb","text_ar":"ثياب"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of linen"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of cotton; not of wool nor of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaz~","text_ar":"خَزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buzuwzN","text_ar":"بُزُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;) meaning, in conjunction with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuzuwzN","text_ar":"خُزُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuzuwzN wa buzuwzN","text_ar":"خُزُوزٌ وَ بُزُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good cloths"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuffs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) [Golius explains it as “Chald."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"בוּץ","text_ar":"בוּץ","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Byssus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"seu potius"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pannus lineus, bombacinus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"etiam"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sericus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"” as on the authority of the S and K (though he omits the explanations in both those lexicons) and Meyd and Ibn-Maaroof (who explains it only by the Persian word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAmaho","text_ar":"جَامَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cotton"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"linen cloth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":") and the Mirkát el-Loghah. He seems to have judged from its resemblance in sound to the Chaldee and Latin words with which he identifies it. The things which it signifies, however, may perhaps be so called because they are usual spoils: and hence also, perhaps, the application here next following.]       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weapons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arms;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a weapon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silaAHN","text_ar":"سِلَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biz~apN","text_ar":"بِزَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bazazN","text_ar":"بَزَزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biz~iyzaY","text_ar":"بِزِّيزَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the first of these four words including in its application"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coats of mail and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migofar","text_ar":"مِغْفَر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the sword:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sword:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, A, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bazazN","text_ar":"بَزَزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to AA,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complete arms."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqal~ada baz~aA HasanFA","text_ar":"تَقَلَّدَ بَزَّا حَسَنًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hung upon himself a goodly sword, putting its suspensory belt or cord upon his neck."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAmilapK","text_ar":"كَامِلَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazaA fiY biz~apK","text_ar":"غَزَا فِى بِزَّةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went to war in complete arms."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)"}],"source_refs":["IAmb","Mgh","K","Lth","Msb","S","A","TA","IDrd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}